    <h3>Status Transitions (IA)</h3>
    <p>Interface Agreements (IA) always relate to a specific Interface (IF) but there can be 1 or more IAs
    for any given IF. Hence, the number of IAs can differ from the number of IFs.</p>
    <p>Furthermore, a specific IA may consist of several <%= help_term 'IA Records'%> - each IA Record
    tracing a new revision or status change of the IA. The previous - normally agreed - IA Record shows 
    the currently valid agreement, the new IA Record is in the workflow to revise the previous agreement
    or to change the status of the previous agreement. The previous IA Record is still valid (as agreement)
    until the new, revised IA (status) becomes effective per mutual agreement.</p>
    <p>In the simple case, an IA is represented by the most recent IA Record. The status of that IA Record
    can be used as status of the IA in total.</p>
    <p>When an IA is in the process of being revised, the IA is represented by two IA Records: The original,
    agreed IA Record is shown together with the new IA Record under revision until the new IA Record 
    replaced the previous IA Record.</p>
